=80=9D Abel=E2=80=99s texts and =E2=80=9Cconspired=E2=80=9D with Lively=E2=
=80=99s team to help them file the complaint. =E2=80=9CFaced with losing ye=
t another client, [Jones] resorted to her well-reported tactics and attempt=
ed to decimate her own client,=E2=80=9D Freedman told me.=C2=A0<br/><br/>If=
 Freedman files a lawsuit, as he has promised, he may very well investigate=
 <em>everyone=E2=80=99s</em> motivations, plus dig into Jones=E2=80=99s wor=
k for and against <strong>Dwayne Johnson</strong> and
<strong>Lauren S=C3=A1nchez</strong> (both former clients) and <strong>Scoo=
ter Braun</strong> (a client who is a financial backer of <strong>Melissa N=
athan</strong>=E2=80=99s P.R. agency, which now reps Baldoni) to establish =
a pattern. The discovery could get messy, and there=E2=80=99s also the poss=
ibility of legal action from Abel over the seizure of her phone.<br/><br/>J=
ones didn=E2=80=99t respond to a request for comment on the matter. But on =
Tuesday, she filed her own lawsuit, accusing Baldoni of breaching a contrac=
t that
called for his company to pay her $25,000 a month through May 2025 and clai=
ming that Abel and Nathan orchestrated the smear campaign against Lively be=
hind her back. Her claim of ignorance is hard to take seriously given that =
on August 14, in the midst of the <em>It Ends With Us</em> backbiting, Jone=
s sent her <em>own</em> strategy email that recommended =E2=80=9Cflooding t=
he zone=E2=80=9D with positive stories about Baldoni as well as mobilizing =
a =E2=80=9Crobust network of supporters and third-party
advocates=E2=80=9D to provide counternarratives to Lively=E2=80=99s allegat=
ions. I=E2=80=99ve obtained Jones=E2=80=99s 8/14 memo, which recommends the=
 team =E2=80=9Cprepare alternative stories.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<br/><br/>Interes=
tingly, it also reveals the leadership of Sony, which released <em>It Ends =
With Us</em>, had begun hunting for leaks regarding the Lively-Baldoni frac=
as, and had accused Jones of having called the <em>Daily Mail</em> and =E2=
=80=9Cescalated things.=E2=80=9D She denied the accusation, but two weeks l=
ater, Jones would be fired, leading her to
email the president of Baldoni=E2=80=99s company: =E2=80=9CAs you are aware=
, we are currently in a contract that does not include a termination clause=
=2E=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Perhaps Jones, with=20=
her new lawsuit, is now trying to g=
et ahead of what=E2=80=99s coming. Either way, this saga is far from over. =
We=E2=80=99re about to get a look behind the curtain of Hollywood=E2=80=99s=
 smear machines=E2=80=94and yes, I used the plural.</li></ul></div>
